Arctic Monkeys postponed concert in Glasgow due to Alex Turner's illness
Rock band Arctic Monkeys moved up the concert in Glasgow after the lead singer was diagnosed with laryngitis.
The Sheffield group was scheduled to perform at the city's Hydro Complex on Friday.
But the illness of lead singer Alex Turner forced her to move the performance.
The group's announcement came after it was similarly forced to postpone Thursday's appearance at the LG Arena in Birmingham.
In a statement on their official website, the Arctic Monkeys said: "After the decision to postpone today's appearance at the LG Arena in Birmingham, and on medical advice, the Arctic Monkeys must also postpone the appearance at the Hydro in Glasgow, scheduled for Friday, 1 November."
"Alex Turner has been diagnosed with laryngeal inflammation, and unfortunately he won't be able to get out."
The performance at the LG Arena in Birmingham will take place on 20 November and a performance at the Hydro in Glasgow complex on 21 November.
All tickets for these performances remain valid.
